urlText: Trackwork Coaches replace the XPT service between Albury and Melbourne

Rail network manager ARTC has implemented speed restrictions on the North East Rail Lines in Victoria. 
To maintain service times and connections with other services the Sydney to Melbourne, Melbourne to Sydney XPT train service has been replaced by road coaches to/from Albury and Melbourne.

  • No trackwork scheduled on the Metro North West Line but trackwork on the City Circle may affect how you travel.

content:
Saturday 18 and Sunday 19 April 
  • Trains run between Berowra and Wynyard only.
  • A shuttle train service also runs between Lindfield and North Sydney.
  • City Circle trains run in one direction only, from Wynyard first stop Town Hall, then continue to T2 Inner West & Leppington and T8 South Line stations.

  • T1 Western and T9 Northern Line trains start and end at Central, platforms 1-12.
